<paragraph id="8B9C36BFFFA8FFFDE137FCECFDA63D19" blockId="3.[264,1325,753,1659]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B957EAADFFA8FFFDE137FCECFDA83A08" box="[312,558,833,858]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Description: Female</emphasis>
: Idiosoma L/W 806/594; Dgl­3 not fused with postoc and D­1; coxal field L 285; Cx­3 W 362; Cx­1+2 mL 78; I­L­5 dL 169, H 35, dL/H ratio 4.83; S­1 L 62, L/W ratio 10.6, S­2 L 71, L/W ratio 13.7, distance between sword setae 3, L ratio S­1/ 2 0.87; I­L­6 L 146, H 28, dL/H ratio 5.2; L ratio I­L­5/6 1.16; genital field L/W 177/144, Ac­1­3 27, 24, 24; chelicera total L 291; palp total L 459, dL and relative L (in parentheses given as % of total length): P­1 34 (7), P­2 116 (25), P­3 109 (24), P­4 150 (33), P­5 50 (11); L ratio P­2/4 0.77.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9C36BFFFA8FFFDE137FBF4FC6D3F01" blockId="3.[264,1325,753,1659]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B957EAADFFA8FFFDE137FBF4FE443D20" box="[312,450,1113,1138]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Discussion:</emphasis>
The Iranian specimen shows a general conformity with 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D3CFFA8FFFDE456FBF4FEC93DC8" baseAuthorityName="Walter" baseAuthorityYear="1947" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="denticulatus">
<emphasis id="B957EAADFFA8FFFDE456FBF4FEC93DC8" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Atractides denticulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the combination of a striated integument, presence of muscle attachment sclerites, sclerotized excretory pore, fused Vgl­1/2, similar morphology of I­L­5 and 6 (
<figureCitation id="13182A3AFFA8FFFDE4DBFB04FA9C3D91" box="[1236,1306,1193,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[264,382,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[308,1302,335,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-85@4.[285,1302,329,1466]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Atractides cf. denticulatus (Walter, 1947), female: 1 = idiosoma, dorsal view; 2 = genital field; 3 = I­L­5/6; 4 = palp, medial view; 5 = palp, lateral view; 6 = I­L­5. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050341/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), IV­L­5 with a long, fine, distal hair (
<figureCitation id="13182A3AFFA8FFFDE2CEFB7CFC8D3DB9" box="[705,779,1233,1259]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[264,382,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[308,1302,335,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-85@4.[285,1302,329,1466]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Atractides cf. denticulatus (Walter, 1947), female: 1 = idiosoma, dorsal view; 2 = genital field; 3 = I­L­5/6; 4 = palp, medial view; 5 = palp, lateral view; 6 = I­L­5. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050341/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), and the shape of palp with denticulation on ventral surface of P­2 and P­3. However, clear morphological differences can be observed between specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F334762FFFA8FFFDE237FA8CFDE13C69" box="[568,615,1313,1339]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Iran</collectingCountry>
and Central Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B4EFFA8FFFDE366FA8CFB933C69" author="Gerecke, R." box="[873,1045,1313,1339]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" pagination="141 - 378" refId="ref3650" refString="Gerecke, R. (2003) Water mite of the genus Atractides Koch, 1837 (Acari: Parasitengona: Hygrobatidae) in the western Palaearctic region: a revision. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 138, 141 - 378." type="journal article" year="2003">Gerecke 2003</bibRefCitation>
). In the specimen from Simk a Dgl­3 is not fused with postoc and D­1 (
<figureCitation id="13182A3AFFA8FFFDE342FAE4FC153C31" box="[845,915,1353,1379]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[264,382,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[308,1302,335,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-85@4.[285,1302,329,1466]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Atractides cf. denticulatus (Walter, 1947), female: 1 = idiosoma, dorsal view; 2 = genital field; 3 = I­L­5/6; 4 = palp, medial view; 5 = palp, lateral view; 6 = I­L­5. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050341/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), the gonopore is more elongated (
<figureCitation id="13182A3AFFA8FFFDE11EFADCFEDA3CD9" box="[273,348,1393,1419]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[264,382,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[308,1302,335,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-85@4.[285,1302,329,1466]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Atractides cf. denticulatus (Walter, 1947), female: 1 = idiosoma, dorsal view; 2 = genital field; 3 = I­L­5/6; 4 = palp, medial view; 5 = palp, lateral view; 6 = I­L­5. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050341/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), and the ventral surface of P­2 and P­3 has a weaker denticulation (
<figureCitation id="13182A3AFFA8FFFDE4ABFADCFA9D3CD9" box="[1188,1307,1393,1419]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[264,382,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[308,1302,335,1465]" captionTargetId="figure-85@4.[285,1302,329,1466]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Atractides cf. denticulatus (Walter, 1947), female: 1 = idiosoma, dorsal view; 2 = genital field; 3 = I­L­5/6; 4 = palp, medial view; 5 = palp, lateral view; 6 = I­L­5. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050341/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Figs. 4, 5</figureCitation>
). Specimens described from 
<collectingCountry id="F334762FFFA8FFFDE244FA34FD363CE1" box="[587,688,1433,1459]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B4EFFA8FFFDE2CFFA34FCE43CE1" author="Petrova, A." box="[704,866,1433,1459]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" pagination="47 - 93" refId="ref4147" refString="Petrova, A. (1968) Hydracariens souterrains de Bulgarie III. (Hydrachnellae, Acari). Bulletin de l'Institut de Zoolgie et Musee, Academie Bulgare des Sciences, 28, 47 - 93." type="journal article" year="1968">Petrova 1968</bibRefCitation>
), based on the shape and arrangement of dorsal sclerites (Dgl­3 not fused with postoc and D­1), more closely resemble the specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F334762FFFA8FFFDE19FFA44FE393F51" box="[400,447,1513,1539]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Iran</collectingCountry>
than the orginal description. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B4EFFA8FFFDE3CEFA44FBFE3F51" author="Gerecke, R." box="[961,1144,1513,1539]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" pagination="141 - 378" refId="ref3650" refString="Gerecke, R. (2003) Water mite of the genus Atractides Koch, 1837 (Acari: Parasitengona: Hygrobatidae) in the western Palaearctic region: a revision. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 138, 141 - 378." type="journal article" year="2003">Gerecke (2003)</bibRefCitation>
future investigations on the geographical variation in 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D3CFFA8FFFDE302F9BCFC433F78" baseAuthorityName="Walter" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[781,965,1553,1578]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="denticulatus">
<emphasis id="B957EAADFFA8FFFDE302F9BCFC433F78" box="[781,965,1553,1578]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">A. denticulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could prove that this taxon represents a species complex. This is the first record from 
<collectingCountry id="F334762FFFA8FFFDE3BAF994FC6E3F01" box="[949,1000,1593,1619]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9C36BFFFA8FFFDE137F9CCFC693F29" blockId="3.[264,1325,753,1659]" box="[312,1007,1633,1659]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B957EAADFFA8FFFDE137F9CCFE413F28" box="[312,455,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Distribution</emphasis>
: Central and south­east Europe, 
<collectingCountry id="F334762FFFA8FFFDE348F9CCFC2A3F29" box="[839,940,1633,1659]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">England</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F334762FFFA8FFFDE3B7F9CCFC6D3F29" box="[952,1003,1633,1659]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
